TY  - JOUR
AU  - Moel, Alberto
AU  - Tufano, Peter
T1  - When Are Real Options Exercised? An Empirical Study of Mine Closings
PY  - 2002
Y1  - 2002/01/01
DO  - 10.1093/rfs/15.1.35
JO  - The Review of Financial Studies
JA  - Rev Financ Stud
VL  - 15
IS  - 1
SP  - 35
EP  - 64
SN  - 0893-9454
AB  - In this article, we study a well-known real option: the opening and closing of mines. Using a new database that tracks the annual opening and closing decisions of 285 developed North American gold mines in the period 1988–1997, we find that the real options model is a useful descriptor of mines’ opening and shutting decisions. In addition, we find that the decision whether to shut a mine is related to firm-specific managerial factors not normally considered within a strict real options model.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rfs/15.1.35
ER  - 



